org.conqat.lib.commons.enums

Class EnumValueMap<E extends java.lang.Enum<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.conqat.lib.commons.enums.EnumValueMap<E>

  • public class EnumValueMap<E extends java.lang.Enum<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a map from enum constant names to its actual enum values.

    This can be used instead of EnumUtils.valueOf() (or .valueOf) for performance reasons, especially if the lookup of constant names is expected to fail often. Otherwise EnumUtils.valueOf() (or .valueOf) have a similar performance.

    In case of looking up strings that do not exist as enum constant EnumUtils has to catch an IllegalArgumentException which has an even bigger performance impact. This implementation simply returns null if the element is not found without this overhead.
